KAAPMUIDEN &#8211; Seven Somalians in their twenties were arrested during a police operation this morning. Police spokesman Brig Leonard Hlathi said the arrest happened on the N4 at around 05:00. &#8220;They were travelling in the direction of the border towards Mbombela when police stopped the bakkie.&#8221;He said police arrested the Somalians on the Immigration Act. Hlathi added that the driver of the vehicle was also arrested for aiding and abetting. Hawks police spokesperson Capt Dineo Sekgotodi said they were still busy investigating the matter further. More details to follow.